# Red Book model routing

Three phases — do not write Bulgarian article prose outside Phase B.

## Phase A — Prep (Auto / Composer)

Steps 1–2 only. Prefer scripts over reasoning.

```bash
.venv/bin/python scripts/select_candidates.py --n 10
.venv/bin/python scripts/prepare_brief.py <ids...>
```

- Run `prepare_brief.py` instead of hand-copying `/tmp/rb/` files.
- **Stop** when `drafts/<id>_<Title>/` exists with `brief.md`, `redbook.txt`, `skeleton.wikitext`.
- Do **not** create `outbox/*.mw` in Phase A.
- End with: *Brief ready for `<Title>`. Switch to Opus for Phase B.*

## Phase B — Write (Opus only)

- Model must be **Claude Opus** (manual picker or `/red-book-writer` subagent).
- Read `TEMPLATE.md`, `drafts/.../brief.md`, `redbook.txt`, `skeleton.wikitext`.
- Output: `outbox/<Bg_Title>.mw` only. No publish scripts yet.

## Phase C — Ship (Auto / Composer)

Steps 4–7 only: `check_links.py`, `publish_api.py`, `link_wikidata_sitelinks.py`, `tracking.csv`, bot log.

Fix link errors with the cheap model; re-run `check_links.py` until clean.

## Hard stops

- Never run `publish_api.py` before `check_links.py` is clean.
- Never write `.mw` prose when the user is on Auto unless they explicitly override.
- If no `drafts/` brief exists, run Phase A first.
